TF-IDF is a term “frequency-inverse document frequency” which is an information retrieval and data mining techniques for common weighting. Combine this technique can let analysis system be more efficiently weight word scores before classification. For example, Delta TFIDF significantly improves accuracy for sentiment analysis problems using three well known data sets. And we can also take advantage of text features of TF-IDF, and by establish SVM forecast system to do sentimental analysis.Reference links for :(1) Paper material : “Delta TFIDF: An Improved Feature Space for Sentiment Analysis“. (2) Blog Code : tfidf for 情感分析





